  "prompt": "What is the legal history of money laundering prohibitions?",
  "response": "The legal history of money laundering prohibitions is complex and has evolved significantly over time. Here's an overview of key developments:\n\n1. Early Origins:\n- Informal money laundering practices existed for centuries\n- Initial focus was on concealing proceeds from illegal activities\n\n2. United States Developments:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) - First major legislative attempt to combat money laundering\n- Required financial institutions to report large currency transactions\n- Established reporting and record-keeping requirements\n\n3. International Developments:\n- 1988 UN Vienna Convention - First international treaty addressing money laundering related to drug trafficking\n- Established framework for international cooperation\n- Encouraged criminalizing money laundering as a distinct offense\n\n4. Key Milestones:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) established in 1989\n- Developed international standards for combating money laundering\n- Created comprehensive recommendations for national legal frameworks\n\n5. Post-9/11 Developments:\n- USA PATRIOT Act (2001) significantly expanded money laundering regulations\n- Increased reporting requirements\n- Enhanced international information sharing\n- Connected anti-money laundering efforts with counter-terrorism financing\n\n6. Ongoing Global Evolution:\n- Continual refinement of legal frameworks\n- Increasing complexity of regulations\n- Growing focus on digital currencies and technological challenges",
